## Task 9: Alignment and Display

**CSS Alignment**

CSS provides properties to control the alignment of elements both horizontally and vertically.

* **Horizontal Alignment:**
    - `text-align`: Aligns the text within an element (left, center, right, justify).
    - `margin-left`, `margin-right`: Adjusts the left and right margins of an element.
    - `padding-left`, `padding-right`: Adjusts the internal padding on the left and right sides of an element.

* **Vertical Alignment:**
    - `vertical-align`: Aligns the content within an element (top, middle, bottom).
    - `margin-top`, `margin-bottom`: Adjusts the top and bottom margins of an element.
    - `padding-top`, `padding-bottom`: Adjusts the internal padding on the top and bottom sides of an element.

**CSS Display Properties**

The `display` property determines how an element is displayed on the page. Common values include:

* **block:** Element is displayed as a block, taking up the full width of its container and starting on a new line.
* **inline:** Element is displayed inline, without starting on a new line.
* **inline-block:** Element is displayed as a block, but without starting on a new line.
* **flex:** Element is part of a flex container, allowing for flexible layout.

**Example:**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Alignment and Display</title>
    <style>
        .container {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .item {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="item">Item 1</div>
        <div class="item">Item 2</div>
        <div class="item">Item 3</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

**Explanation:**

- The `.container` element is set to `display: flex` to create a flex container.
- The `justify-content: space-between` property distributes the items evenly within the container with spaces between them.
- The `align-items: center` property vertically aligns the items in the center of the container.
- The `.item` elements are styled with centered text alignment, padding, and a border.

By combining these alignment techniques and display properties, you can create various layouts and positions for elements on your web page.
